            <title><![CDATA[Switch 2 Price Speculation, A First Look At The Next Battlefield, And More Of The Week's Top News]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/switch-2-price-scalpers-project-ethos-1851758134</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/switch-2-price-speculation-a-first-look-at-the-next-battlefield-and-more-of-the-weeks-top-news.1103967/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/switch-2-price-scalpers-project-ethos-1851758134<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="b4465888910864f528b8e8cda136e211" data-recommend-id="image://b4465888910864f528b8e8cda136e211" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->EA / Dice / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Universal / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Konami / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo<!-- -->, <!-- -->2K Games / Valve / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Saber Interactive<!-- -->, <!-- -->Valve / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->2K Games / Activision</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="b4465888910864f528b8e8cda136e211" data-recommend-id="image://b4465888910864f528b8e8cda136e211" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Our next official look at the Switch 2 is still a few months off, but that hasn’t stopped folks from speculating about its price, or obsessing over the details we may have gleaned about the packaging its games will come in. Elsewhere, EA gave us a (very brief!) first look at the next <em>Battlefield </em>and shared details on how folks can play it early, and the release date for the remake of <em>Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater </em>was prematurely revealed. Read on for these stories and more.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="0e15ef433f6621be5c5e2aaff999de07" data-recommend-id="image://0e15ef433f6621be5c5e2aaff999de07" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->EA / Dice / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="0e15ef433f6621be5c5e2aaff999de07" data-recommend-id="image://0e15ef433f6621be5c5e2aaff999de07" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>EA has pulled back the curtain on the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/battlefield-6-modern-day-specialists-classes-release-da-1851649399?_gl=1*otu5he*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODU5ODA3OS4xNjQuMS4xNzM4NjAxNjk1LjU3LjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/battlefield-6-modern-day-specialists-classes-release-da-1851649399?_gl=1*otu5he*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODU5ODA3OS4xNjQuMS4xNzM4NjAxNjk1LjU3LjAuMA..">next mainline entry</a></span> in its long-running <em>Battlefield </em>franchise, explaining a new development plan involving four different studios, as well as a new way for players to hop in early to provide feedback on what the teams are making.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ea-battlefield-6-first-gameplay-beta-labs-studios-bf3-4-1851753963?_gl=1*159v4hg*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODkzODY1OS40MDQuMS4xNzM4OTU2NDE2LjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ea-battlefield-6-first-gameplay-beta-labs-studios-bf3-4-1851753963?_gl=1*159v4hg*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODkzODY1OS40MDQuMS4xNzM4OTU2NDE2LjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4742535a5c83a7db895957552eab1969" data-recommend-id="image://4742535a5c83a7db895957552eab1969" data-format="jpg" data-width="1459" data-height="821" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario races against Peach and Bowser. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mario races against Peach and Bowser. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4742535a5c83a7db895957552eab1969" data-recommend-id="image://4742535a5c83a7db895957552eab1969" data-format="jpg" data-width="1459" data-height="821" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario races against Peach and Bowser. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>When Switch cases arrived back in 2017, they looked comically unnecessary. The SD cards the games were installed on were tiny while the plastic surrounding them was exponentially bigger. Most cases didn’t even come with anything else inside. I’ve enjoyed collecting them but they were a huge waste. According to a new leak, the Switch 2 cases might be even worse. - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-game-case-size-physical-cartridge-nintendo-1851754196&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-game-case-size-physical-cartridge-nintendo-1851754196">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3bf499ac535ae72b41db7d8578251183" data-recommend-id="image://3bf499ac535ae72b41db7d8578251183" data-format="png" data-width="944" data-height="502" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario and Luigi are shocked at Switch 2 prices. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mario and Luigi are shocked at Switch 2 prices. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Universal / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3bf499ac535ae72b41db7d8578251183" data-recommend-id="image://3bf499ac535ae72b41db7d8578251183" data-format="png" data-width="944" data-height="502" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario and Luigi are shocked at Switch 2 prices. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-preorder-scalper-ebay-reseller-date-1851754702&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-preorder-scalper-ebay-reseller-date-1851754702">The Switch 2</a></span> currently faces three big questions following its <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-switch-2-release-date-april-2025-1851740848&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-direct-switch-2-release-date-april-2025-1851740848">January reveal</a></span>: how powerful is it, what games will it have, and what will it cost? Nintendo was asked about that last one in its latest earnings call, and while the company’s president remained cagey, he also said Nintendo will continue to take its reputation for affordability into account when determining the final price, which some experts predict will be $400.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-preorder-mk9-1851755723&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-price-release-date-preorder-mk9-1851755723">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="ef71e1197684fc9bc1c4a0f138c8fe8a" data-recommend-id="image://ef71e1197684fc9bc1c4a0f138c8fe8a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->2K Games / Valve / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="ef71e1197684fc9bc1c4a0f138c8fe8a" data-recommend-id="image://ef71e1197684fc9bc1c4a0f138c8fe8a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>This year marks the 20th anniversary of <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/michael-condrey-projet-ethos-31st-union-2k-games-1851756173&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/michael-condrey-projet-ethos-31st-union-2k-games-1851756173">2K Games</a></span>. Normally we don’t celebrate publisher birthdays, but we’ll make an exception this time as 2K Games is honoring the milestone with a big sale on Steam that has one particularly noteworthy offer: a package that includes 20 games for $20. Is this an incredible deal? Maybe.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/steam-sale-2k-civ-borderlands-mafia-pc-20-for-20-deal-1851757287&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/steam-sale-2k-civ-borderlands-mafia-pc-20-for-20-deal-1851757287">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="8997bcdff410a320304a57d189ed8068" data-recommend-id="image://8997bcdff410a320304a57d189ed8068" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Switch 2 patent appears on the screen of a Switch 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Switch 2 patent appears on the screen of a Switch 2. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="8997bcdff410a320304a57d189ed8068" data-recommend-id="image://8997bcdff410a320304a57d189ed8068" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Switch 2 patent appears on the screen of a Switch 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Fans have been speculating about <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-pc-mouse-joycon-civilization-7-1851741008&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-pc-mouse-joycon-civilization-7-1851741008">PC gaming mouse-like functionality for the Switch 2</a></span> ever since optical sensors appeared in leaks last month. Nintendo then teased the feature in the new Switch’s reveal trailer shortly after. Now the potential game-changer has been all but officially announced thanks to a new patent breaking down how  the Joy-Con mouse functionality will work. - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-joycon-mouse-pc-civ-7-halo-nintendo-direct-1851757351&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-joycon-mouse-pc-civ-7-halo-nintendo-direct-1851757351">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="d45cf4987318be7972cc287fa25a2130" data-recommend-id="image://d45cf4987318be7972cc287fa25a2130" data-format="png" data-width="2000" data-height="1125" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Space Marine looks out at the stars. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Space Marine looks out at the stars. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Saber Interactive</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d45cf4987318be7972cc287fa25a2130" data-recommend-id="image://d45cf4987318be7972cc287fa25a2130" data-format="png" data-width="2000" data-height="1125" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Space Marine looks out at the stars. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/space-marine-2-warhammer-40k-review-how-long-review-ps5-1851639029?_gl=1*18hazyp*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODg2NjU0My4yNDQuMC4xNzM4ODY2NTQ1LjU4LjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/space-marine-2-warhammer-40k-review-how-long-review-ps5-1851639029?_gl=1*18hazyp*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODg2NjU0My4yNDQuMC4xNzM4ODY2NTQ1LjU4LjAuMA.."><em>Warhammer 40,000: Space Marine 2</em></a></span> received multiple 2024 Game Awards nominations and sold over five million copies. But its makers say the visually impressive old-school-feeling sci-fi shooter cost only a quarter of what’s needed to make most big-budget AAA blockbusters. Developed by Saber Interactive, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/space-marine-2-saber-ceo-asmongold-youtube-comment-1851650858&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/space-marine-2-saber-ceo-asmongold-youtube-comment-1851650858">the company’s CEO</a></span>, Matt Karch, thinks this model is the future.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/warhammer-40k-space-marine-2-saber-matt-karch-budgets-1851756857&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/warhammer-40k-space-marine-2-saber-matt-karch-budgets-1851756857">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="13b958cc012b03ba028df18e087103ea" data-recommend-id="image://13b958cc012b03ba028df18e087103ea" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Michael Condrey appears beside a screenshot for Project Ethos. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Michael Condrey appears beside a screenshot for Project Ethos. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->2K Games / Activision</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="13b958cc012b03ba028df18e087103ea" data-recommend-id="image://13b958cc012b03ba028df18e087103ea" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Michael Condrey appears beside a screenshot for Project Ethos. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>2K Games has fired 31st Union president  Michael Condrey after the studio’s long-awaited <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/project-ethos-2k-games-twitch-f2p-fortnite-overwatch-1851675279&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/project-ethos-2k-games-twitch-f2p-fortnite-overwatch-1851675279">online multiplayer game <em>Project Ethos</em></a></span> was revealed last fall to little fanfare or apparent player interest, according to two sources familiar with the studio. The project’s fate is now unclear, although 2K, which is publishing <em>Borderlands 4</em> and <em>Mafia: The Old Country</em> later this year, says it remains “very committed” to both <em>Project Ethos</em> and the studio behind it.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/michael-condrey-projet-ethos-31st-union-2k-games-1851756173&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/michael-condrey-projet-ethos-31st-union-2k-games-1851756173">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="abb7b39ab36fba5749dd8a90af191c8a" data-recommend-id="image://abb7b39ab36fba5749dd8a90af191c8a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1551" data-height="873" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The most solid of snakes points a gun toward us, while hiding behind caterpillar tracks." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The most solid of snakes points a gun toward us, while hiding behind caterpillar tracks." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Konami / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="abb7b39ab36fba5749dd8a90af191c8a" data-recommend-id="image://abb7b39ab36fba5749dd8a90af191c8a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1551" data-height="873" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The most solid of snakes points a gun toward us, while hiding behind caterpillar tracks." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>When information is leaked by nefarious means, companies open a firehose of takedown notices to try to regain control. It’s always a bit disappointing that they don’t do the same when the leak’s coming from inside the house. Such is the case for <em>Metal Gear Solid Delta: Snake Eater</em>, after Sony seemingly accidentally uploaded <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://vulcan.dl.playstation.net/img/rnd/202502/0611/2c429928f5c5b20df3c78f5053ace69c011d4f391782ab47.mp4&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://vulcan.dl.playstation.net/img/rnd/202502/0611/2c429928f5c5b20df3c78f5053ace69c011d4f391782ab47.mp4" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">a trailer</a></span> that contains the release date straight to the front page of your PS5. Konami, send angry threats to Sony! - John Walker <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/metal-gear-solid-delta-snake-eater-release-date-leak-1851756726&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/metal-gear-solid-delta-snake-eater-release-date-leak-1851756726">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="915373bce1d4be90cacbea2708ce01bd" data-recommend-id="image://915373bce1d4be90cacbea2708ce01bd" data-format="png" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows new Valve warnings for Early Access. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows new Valve warnings for Early Access. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Valve / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="915373bce1d4be90cacbea2708ce01bd" data-recommend-id="image://915373bce1d4be90cacbea2708ce01bd" data-format="png" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot shows new Valve warnings for Early Access. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Have you ever come across an Early Access game on Steam, decided it looked pretty cool and downloaded it, only to realize it was kind of busted and never getting updated again? <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://steamcommunity.com/discussions/forum/0/6257258782500903675/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://steamcommunity.com/discussions/forum/0/6257258782500903675/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">It’s long been a topic among PC players</a></span>, and Valve now has a new tool to hopefully reduce such occurrences. A warning on Steam pages for Early Access games will now tell prospective buyers how long it’s been since the game was last updated.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/steam-early-access-warning-abandoned-unsung-story-1851756411&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/steam-early-access-warning-abandoned-unsung-story-1851756411">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="89b29a15c159658295ec43d1ffb13383" data-recommend-id="image://89b29a15c159658295ec43d1ffb13383" data-format="jpg" data-width="1629" data-height="916" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario jumps next to a Switch 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mario jumps next to a Switch 2. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="89b29a15c159658295ec43d1ffb13383" data-recommend-id="image://89b29a15c159658295ec43d1ffb13383" data-format="jpg" data-width="1629" data-height="916" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario jumps next to a Switch 2. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>There’s a lot we still don’t know about the Switch 2, but one sure bet is that it will sell like bonkers when it first launches. If there are any initial shortages whatsoever, scalpers will be looking to flip the new console on eBay and other sites for hundreds over the asking price. Nintendo says it’s making preparations to try to avoid the Switch 2 being the latest casualty of the modern online pre-order hellscape.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-preorder-scalper-ebay-reseller-date-1851754702?_gl=1*35ohy9*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODkzODY1OS40MDQuMS4xNzM4OTU2NDE2LjYwLjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-preorder-scalper-ebay-reseller-date-1851754702?_gl=1*35ohy9*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODkzODY1OS40MDQuMS4xNzM4OTU2NDE2LjYwLjAuMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
